  "prompt": "What are some good NGOs working in the field of children's education in India?",
  "response": "There are several reputable NGOs in India focusing on children's education. Here are some well-known ones:\n\n1. **Pratham**: One of the largest non-governmental organizations in India, Pratham focuses on providing quality education to underprivileged children. Their flagship program, the Annual Status of Education Report (ASER), assesses the learning outcomes of children across rural India.\n\n2. **Teach For India**: Part of the global Teach For All network, Teach For India recruits bright young individuals to teach in under-resourced schools for two years, aiming to bridge educational inequities.\n\n3. **Aga Khan Foundation**: This organization works towards improving the quality of education in India through various community-based programs and partnerships with local governments.\n\n4. **CRY - Child Rights and You**: While CRY addresses various issues concerning children's rights, a significant focus is on education. They work to create sustainable changes and ensure children have access to quality education.\n\n5. **Save the Children India**: This organization runs several initiatives to ensure all children have the opportunity to learn and grow. They focus on early childhood care, basic education, and adolescent education.\n\n6. **Room to Read**: It focuses on literacy and gender equality in education. Their Literacy Program aims to develop reading skills and a habit of reading among primary school children.\n\n7. **Azim Premji Foundation**: This foundation works to improve education across India by partnering with the government and running their schools and universities to demonstrate best practices.\n\n8. **Goonj**: While primarily known for disaster relief, Goonj also works on rural education, aiming to improve infrastructure and provide resources to under-served schools.\n\n9. **Smile Foundation**: This organization runs the \"Mission Education\" program to provide education and healthcare support to underserved children across India.\n\n10. **Bharti Foundation**: The philanthropic arm of Bharti Enterprises, they focus on quality education through their Satya Bharti School Program, especially in rural areas.\n\nThese NGOs have different approaches and areas of focus, so it's worth exploring which aligns best with your interests or needs if you're considering support or collaboration.",
